Peru (Piura region). 14 Feb 2018. (conf.) cases increased to 4, each in a different location.
https://peru21.pe/peru/suben-cuatro-casos-autoctonos-chikungunya-piura-395901 [in Spanish]

Africa
---
Kenya
- Mombasa county. WHO. 27 Feb 2018. (susp.) 421 cases, (conf.) 32 cases. Subcounties affected: Mvita, Kisauni, Nyali, Changamwe, Jomvu, and Likoni, and one in Kilifi. The majority of suspected cases reported from Mvita and Likoni in Mombasa. Increasing.
http://www.who.int/csr/don/27-february-2018-chikungunya-kenya/en/

[Maps of Kenya: https://goo.gl/pcUuf4 and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5758774,174

A 30 Mar 2018 report indicated that 85 percent of 600 ethnic Aweer families, also known as Boni, in Basuba ward, Mombasa county, have suspected chikungunya virus infections since early March 2018.
https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/health/article/2001274977/viral-fever-hits-boni-forest-community. - Mod.TY]

- Lamu county. 14 Feb 2018. (conf.) 4 cases.
https://www.the-star.co.ke/news/2018/02/14/four-cases-of-chikungunya-virus-reported-in-lamu_c1714508

[It is interesting to remember that chikungunya outbreaks started on the Kenyan coast in 2004-2005 with Lamu island's attack rate at 75 percent. - Roland Hübner. - Mod.TY]

